name: Ophelia Entering the NFT Metaverse
description:
544x799 pixels jpg from rotated 799x544 pixels jpg Wikimedia Commons faithful photographic reproduction of the two-dimensional, public domain work of art "Ophelia" (circa 1851) by John Everett Millais depicting ms. Elizabeth Siddal shot by an unknown photographer for Tate Britain who claims copyright in United Kingdom on this digital reproduction even if the official position taken by the Wikimedia Foundation is that "faithful reproductions of two-dimensional public domain works of art are public domain".

So if you are in UK to stay safe it might be better not to use this image.
